at the hellhole I cook at, but the other one

348
00:15:16,877 --> 00:15:19,210
是在一个好公司的不错的工作
was a good job at a nice company.

349
00:15:19,279 --> 00:15:22,147
三源化学药剂销毁工厂
Trine Chemical Agent Destruction Plant.

350
00:15:22,215 --> 00:15:23,893
Keenan是我们家族里
Keenan was the only one in our family

351
00:15:23,917 --> 00:15:26,284
唯一一个能通过他们要求的背景审查的人
who could actually pass the required background check.

352
00:15:26,353 --> 00:15:28,553
他从没有过犯罪记录
He never had a criminal record.

353
00:15:28,622 --> 00:15:32,357
我们认为他的工作可能和他的死亡有一定的关系
We think that his job might have something to do with his death.

354
00:15:32,425 --> 00:15:34,670
-他是给他们开卡车的 -他提到过氯气吗
- He was driving trucks for them. - He ever mention chlorine?

355
00:15:34,694 --> 00:15:36,572
他的工作包括处理危险的东西吗
Did his job include handling anything dangerous?

356
00:15:36,596 --> 00:15:39,030
如果你想了解化学相关的 去和那家公司谈
If you want to know about chemicals, talk to the company.

357
00:15:39,099 --> 00:15:40,999
我们也在做 但是
We are. But...

358
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:42,834
Keenan没有把事情搞砸
Keenan didn't screw up.

359
00:15:44,471 --> 00:15:47,839
我可以指责我的弟弟 你们不能
I get to blame my baby brother. You don't.

360
00:15:49,876 --> 00:15:52,010
这地方跟诺克斯堡似得
<i>This place is like Fort Knox.</i>

361
00:15:52,078 --> 00:15:54,412
当然 化学物品也可能和黄金一样值钱
Well, chemicals can be just as valuable as gold.

362
00:15:54,481 --> 00:15:56,347
当然也更加危险
Certainly more dangerous.

363
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:59,584
我在想是谁在看着 看到那个了吗
I wonder who's watching. See there?

364
00:15:59,653 --> 00:16:01,386
你好 打扰一下
Hi. Excuse me.

365
00:16:01,454 --> 00:16:03,254
你们一定是NCIS的人了
You must be NCIS.

366
00:16:03,323 --> 00:16:06,591
抱歉来的太晚了 我是一路穿过整个厂区走过来的
My apologies for being so late. I was all the way across campus.

367
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,893
而且 他们给了我们这种高尔夫球车
And, uh, they give us these golf carts,

368
00:16:08,962 --> 00:16:12,530
但为什么要浪费能源呢 对吧 我是Patton Hartgrave博士
but why waste the energy, right? Dr. Patton Hartgrave.

369
00:16:12,599 --> 00:16:14,833
你好 也是三源的首席化学工程师
Hi. Trine's lead chemical engineer.

370
00:16:14,901 --> 00:16:16,434
那么
So...

371
00:16:16,503 --> 00:16:17,936
抱歉
Excuse me.

372
00:16:18,004 --> 00:16:19,904
如果你们不担心看上去显得太笨的话
If you, uh, aren't afraid to look too dorky,

373
00:16:19,973 --> 00:16:21,372
我可以带你参观一下
I could show you around.

374
00:16:21,441 --> 00:16:24,008
我绝不可能看上去笨笨的
It's impossible for me to look dorky.

375
00:16:24,077 --> 00:16:26,444
你说是就是吧
Right.

376
00:16:26,513 --> 00:16:29,914
这里就是见证奇迹的地方
So this is where the magic happens.

377
00:16:29,983 --> 00:16:34,052
我们用两种方式处理有害的化学品
We dispose of harmful chemicals two ways: incineration

378
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:36,888
焚烧和中和 混入其他试剂
and neutralization, mixing in other agents

379
00:16:36,957 --> 00:16:38,723
来消除毒性
to eliminate toxicity.

380
00:16:38,792 --> 00:16:41,759
都是非常有效 非常安全的
It's all very effective, very safe.

381
00:16:41,828 --> 00:16:43,628
这也意味着昂贵的花费
Which means it's very expensive.

382
00:16:43,697 --> 00:16:46,264
我向你保证每一分钱都是值得的
Well, I can assure you it's worth every penny.

383
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:48,466
Keenan Grant在哪儿工作
Where did Keenan Grant work?

384
00:16:50,203 --> 00:16:52,136
好吧
Right.

385
00:16:52,205 --> 00:16:55,540
这个 这个是Grant先生的储物柜
This is, uh... this is Mr. Grant's locker.

386
00:16:55,609 --> 00:16:58,376
我和他本人不熟
I didn't know him personally,

387
00:16:58,445 --> 00:17:00,812
但是当然了 我们听到了发生的事情时都很震惊
but of course, we're all very shocked to hear what happened.

388
00:17:00,881 --> 00:17:02,580
两个晚上之前他在工作吗
Was he working two nights ago?

389
00:17:02,649 --> 00:17:04,482
呃 让我们看看
Uh, let's see.

390
00:17:04,551 --> 00:17:09,554
实际上 我有权查看那些记录
Actually, I have access to those records.

391
00:17:09,623 --> 00:17:12,323
呣
Mm...

392
00:17:12,392 --> 00:17:16,327
哦 是的 看起来他那天晚上是在工作
Uh, yes. It looks like he was working that night.

393
00:17:16,396 --> 00:17:19,764
是去特区的佛蒙特旅馆取货
It was a single pickup at the Freemont Inn in D.C.

394
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,299
那里也是他的尸体被发现的地方
That's where his body was found.

395
00:17:21,368 --> 00:17:23,568
他是要去取什么货
What was he picking up?

396
00:17:23,637 --> 00:17:26,070
一些用于再循环的工业塑料
Some industrial plastic for recycling.

397
00:17:26,139 --> 00:17:27,672
不是什么危险品
It's nothing too dangerous.

398
00:17:27,741 --> 00:17:31,075
是酒店的垃圾 又不是去切尔诺贝利
It's hotel waste, not Chernobyl, which...

399
00:17:31,144 --> 00:17:34,646
那是个没人当回事的生态警示
was an ecological warning sign nobody took seriously enough.

400
00:17:34,714 --> 00:17:36,748
你作为一个化学家似乎
You seem very, uh, Earth-friendly

401
00:17:36,816 --> 00:17:38,483
很关心地球生态保护
for a chemical guy.

402
00:17:38,551 --> 00:17:42,420
嘿 我只是在纠正人类犯下的一些最糟的错误之一
Hey, I'm just correcting some of mankind's worst mistakes.

403
00:17:42,489 --> 00:17:44,122
比如销毁氯气
Like destroying chlorine gas.

404
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:46,491
那时不可能的
That's impossible.

405
00:17:46,559 --> 00:17:50,862
噢 呃 McGee探员和Torres探员 这位是George Ashley Green
Oh, uh, Agents McGee and Torres, this is George Ashley Green,

406
00:17:50,931 --> 00:17:52,497
我们无畏的领导
our fearless leader.

407
00:17:52,565 --> 00:17:55,133
而且也是三源化学的首席执行官
Well, CEO of Trine Chemical, anyway.

408
00:17:55,201 --> 00:17:57,001
我刚好看到你们两个进来了
I happened to see you two come in.

409
00:17:57,070 --> 00:17:58,636
我就知道有人在盯着
I knew somebody was watching.

410
00:17:58,705 --> 00:18:00,625
为什么毁掉氯气是不可能的
Why is destroying chlorine gas impossible?

411
00:18:00,674 --> 00:18:03,775
因为我们多年都没有氯气了
Because we haven't had any for years.

412
00:18:03,843 --> 00:18:05,877
按照之前每次的军事合同
It was all destroyed per previous

413
00:18:05,946 --> 00:18:07,045
都全部处理掉了
military contracts.

414
00:18:07,113 --> 00:18:08,157
当前的合同呢
What about current contracts?

415
00:18:08,181 --> 00:18:09,948
没有和氯气相关的
None, for chlorine.

416
00:18:10,016 --> 00:18:12,951
但没有许可我也只能说这么多了
But that's all I can really say without clearance.

417
00:18:13,019 --> 00:18:14,552
这关乎国家安全
National security concerns.

418
00:18:14,621 --> 00:18:15,987
你能理解的
You understand.

419
00:18:16,056 --> 00:18:17,555
我需要五角大楼的批准
I need permission from the Pentagon.

420
00:18:22,295 --> 00:18:23,561
嘿 Bishop 说
Hey, Bishop. Go.

421
00:18:23,630 --> 00:18:24,941
国防部又在
The DoD is pushing

422
00:18:24,965 --> 00:18:27,131
推迟你的会面时间了
your meeting time, again.

423
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,466
实际上 他们取消了会见
Actually, they cancelled

424
00:18:28,535 --> 00:18:30,068
并且建议你明天再来
and suggested you come back tomorrow.

425
00:18:30,136 --> 00:18:31,803
噢 不 不 不 不
Oh, no. No, no, no.

426
00:18:31,871 --> 00:18:33,805
在得到一些答复之前我是不会走的
I'm not going anywhere until I get some answers.

427
00:18:33,873 --> 00:18:35,551
我跟他们也是这么说的 但他们一直重复
That's what I told them, but they kept citing

428
00:18:35,575 --> 00:18:38,676
这关乎国家安全而不说什么详情
"national security concerns" without any details.

429
00:18:38,745 --> 00:18:40,378
呃 Bishop
Uh, Bishop?

430
00:18:40,447 --> 00:18:42,714
我之后再联系你
I'll call you back.

431
00:18:43,984 --> 00:18:45,750
下午好
Good afternoon.

432
00:18:45,819 --> 00:18:47,085
特别探员Gibbs 对吗
Special Agent Gibbs, right?

433
00:18:47,153 --> 00:18:48,820
Wynn Crawford
Wynn Crawford.

434
00:18:48,888 --> 00:18:50,021
-是的 先生 -我刚和海军部长
- Yes, sir. - I just got done

435
00:18:50,090 --> 00:18:52,223
聊过你的队伍
talking about your team with SECNAV.

436
00:18:52,292 --> 00:18:55,026
她讲了不少关于你的故事 都是好事
She had quite a few stories about you, all good.

437
00:18:55,095 --> 00:18:57,028
-我想也是 -关于你的会面
- I'll bet. - About your meeting...

438
00:18:57,097 --> 00:18:58,596
-呃 被取消了 -是我取消的
- Uh, it was cancelled. - By me.

439
00:18:58,665 --> 00:18:59,945
但既然你在这里了 我想
But since you're here, I figured

440
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,310
我还是当面告诉你这个坏消息吧
I'd give you the bad news in person.

441
00:19:01,334 --> 00:19:03,401
五角大楼的记录已经被临时封锁了
Pentagon records have been temporarily locked.

442
00:19:03,470 --> 00:19:05,636
-被你封锁的 -不 是政府部门
- By you. - No, by State.

443
00:19:05,705 --> 00:19:07,216
他们目前正在和联合国合作
They're currently working with the U.N.

444
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:09,073
达成关于叙利亚的停火协议
on a cease-fire agreement in Syria.

445
00:19:09,142 --> 00:19:11,542
你的请求传递出了危险信息
Your requests sent up red flags.

446
00:19:11,611 --> 00:19:14,412
化学武器的调查让人们很紧张
Chemical weapons investigations make people nervous.

447
00:19:14,481 --> 00:19:16,047
化学袭击也一样
So do chemical attacks.

448
00:19:16,116 --> 00:19:17,749
没错 你瞧 这正是我们
Yeah, see, that's exactly

449
00:19:17,817 --> 00:19:20,184
无法承担的不计后果的谈话
the kind of reckless talk that we can't afford.

450
00:19:20,253 --> 00:19:21,519
现在 你有证据表明存在
Now, do you have proof

451
00:19:21,588 --> 00:19:22,588
有预期的恐怖主义活动吗
of intended terrorism?

452
00:19:22,655 --> 00:19:24,022
还是有武器失踪
Or missing weapons?

453
00:19:24,090 --> 00:19:25,590
你让找证据变得困难了
You're making it hard to find proof.

454
00:19:25,658 --> 00:19:27,737
那你就换种方式找证据 我会很高兴提供帮助的
Well, find a different way, and I'll be happy to help.

455
00:19:27,761 --> 00:19:30,228
我想为你们的受害者寻求正义
I want justice for your victim.

456
00:19:30,296 --> 00:19:32,063
但是陆战队员之间 我说个真话
But Marine to Marine?

457
00:19:32,132 --> 00:19:35,233
世界舞台上 这会儿还有很多更大的事情正在发生
There are a lot bigger things at play here on the world stage.

458
00:19:35,301 --> 00:19:37,435
我们可以两者兼顾的 部长先生
We can do both, Mr. Secretary.

459
00:19:37,504 --> 00:19:40,872
我说这些只是出于礼貌 而不是跟你讨价还价
This was a courtesy, not a negotiation.

460
00:19:40,940 --> 00:19:42,774
现在 除非NCIS
Now, unless NCIS

461
00:19:42,842 --> 00:19:47,745
有确凿证据证明武器失踪了 我说的是真正意义上的武器
has concrete evidence of missing weapons-- actual weapons--

462
00:19:47,814 --> 00:19:49,580
否则 你们就要停止行动
you will stand down.

463
00:19:51,217 --> 00:19:53,151
这是命令
That's an order.

464
00:20:00,660 --> 00:20:03,661
所以 Gibbs把我让你们停止行动的命令
So, Gibbs told you about my order

465
00:20:03,730 --> 00:20:06,164
告诉了你们 然而你们依然没有服从
to stand down, and you still failed to follow it.

466
00:20:06,232 --> 00:20:09,000
我自己也经常不同意Gibbs的做法 长官
I don't always agree with Gibbs myself, sir,

467
00:20:09,069 --> 00:20:10,935
但是我相信他的判断
but I do trust his judgment,

468
00:20:11,004 --> 00:20:13,738
还有我NCIS的同事们的判断
and the judgment of my people here at NCIS.

469
00:20:13,773 --> 00:20:14,784
如果他们没有服从你的命令 那是因为
If they didn't follow your order, it's because

470
00:20:14,808 --> 00:20:16,441
确实有武器失踪了
there are missing weapons.

471
00:20:16,509 --> 00:20:18,776
而这个坐在审讯室里的化学工程师
And the chemical engineer sitting in interrogation...

472
00:20:18,845 --> 00:20:20,812
-他会告诉我们一切吗 -继续看
- Can tell us everything? - Keep watching.

473
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,413
我的人知道怎么击溃他
My people know how to break this guy.

474
00:20:22,482 --> 00:20:24,282
我什么都不说
I'm not saying a word,

475
00:20:24,350 --> 00:20:25,616
所以要么逮捕我 要么放我走
so just arrest me or be done.

476
00:20:25,685 --> 00:20:26,851
很抱歉
I'm sorry,

477
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,286
我们耽误你什么事儿了吗
are we keeping you from something?

478
00:20:28,354 --> 00:20:29,687
你还有约会什么的吗
Hot date, maybe?

479
00:20:36,763 --> 00:20:38,763
哦 天哪
Oh, God!

480
00:20:40,066 --> 00:20:41,866
露馅了
Cat's out of the bag.

481
00:20:41,935 --> 00:20:45,169
我想你们可以说我跟大地母亲有个约会
Guess you could say my hot date's with Mother Earth.

482
00:20:45,238 --> 00:20:46,704
约会地点是地下的棺材里面
Six feet under.

483
00:20:46,773 --> 00:20:48,306
你之前被暴露在毒气中了
You were exposed to the gas.

484
00:20:48,374 --> 00:20:51,142
剂量不多 但是足够致死了
Not much, but enough.

485
00:20:53,246 --> 00:20:56,314
我会在你们逼我交代之前死掉
I'll be dead before you can get me to talk.

486
00:20:56,382 --> 00:20:57,448
我去拿急救箱
I'll get the kit.

487
00:20:57,517 --> 00:20:58,883
抱歉
Sorry.

488
00:20:58,952 --> 00:21:01,018
我猜 NCIS已经没什么能做的了
Well, I guess NCIS is done here.

489
00:21:12,206 --> 00:21:13,350
你需要医疗救护
You need medical attention.

490
00:21:13,374 --> 00:21:14,607
我们正在呼叫医疗人员
We're calling the paramedics.

491
00:21:14,675 --> 00:21:16,020
不 已经太晚了
No, no, no, it's too late for that.

492
00:21:16,044 --> 00:21:17,676
我说过我不想接受急救
I told you I don't want that.

493
00:21:17,745 --> 00:21:19,512
这个人正在咳血
The fact that this man is coughing up blood

494
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:21,147
这就意味着我们是对的
means that we are right.

495
00:21:21,215 --> 00:21:23,449
长官 现在依然有很多遗失的氯气
Sir, there is missing chlorine gas,

496
00:21:23,518 --> 00:21:24,850
这个人知道氯气在哪
and this man knows where it is.

497
00:21:24,919 --> 00:21:27,787
你们又是怎么发现的
And you found this out how?

498
00:21:27,855 --> 00:21:30,322
你们好像忘记了故事里面
You seem to have forgotten the part of the story

499
00:21:30,391 --> 00:21:32,031
你们俩违反了联邦法律的部分
where you two committed a federal offense.

500
00:21:32,060 --> 00:21:33,500
实际上 如果我不了解情况的话
In fact, if I didn't know any better,

501
00:21:33,561 --> 00:21:35,327
我会说你们是在故意拖延时间
I'd say you're deliberately stalling.

502
00:21:35,396 --> 00:21:37,563
-完全没有 -不可能
- Not at all. - No way.

503
00:21:37,632 --> 00:21:40,466
约会习惯 短信息 免费的小玩意儿
Dating habits, text messages, free gadgets.

504
00:21:40,535 --> 00:21:42,902
这些难道是你们NCIS的工作日常吗
These are all essential to your work here at NCIS?

505
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:45,638
实际上 没错
Actually, yeah.

506
00:21:45,706 --> 00:21:47,506
-嘿 Nick -怎么了
- Hey, Nick. - What up?

507
00:21:47,575 --> 00:21:50,409
是你取消了我昨晚的约会吗
Did you cancel my date last night?

508
00:21:50,478 --> 00:21:51,544
早上好
Good morning.

509
00:21:51,612 --> 00:21:53,245
我昨晚应该出去约会的
I was supposed to have a date last night,

510
00:21:53,314 --> 00:21:56,982
但是据Boyd所说 我把约会取消了
but according to Boyd, I cancelled it.

511
00:21:57,051 --> 00:21:58,551
你没跟我商量
You sent a message

512
00:21:58,619 --> 00:22:00,753
-就发了信息 -Gibbs当时就站在那里
- without telling me. - Gibbs was standing right there.

513
00:22:00,822 --> 00:22:01,865
你想让我怎么做 让你陷入麻烦吗
What do you want me to do, let you get in trouble?

514
00:22:01,889 --> 00:22:04,090
就为了条信息吗
For getting a text message?

515
00:22:04,158 --> 00:22:05,424
这根本说不过去
That doesn't make any sense.

516
00:22:05,493 --> 00:22:07,026
他甚至不知道信息是谁发的
He didn't even know who it was from.

517
00:22:07,095 --> 00:22:08,594
没错 而且他对这事儿没兴趣
Yeah, he didn't care, either.

518
00:22:08,629 --> 00:22:10,463
五角大楼的记录 什么情况了
Pentagon records. Go.

519
00:22:10,531 --> 00:22:13,199
我们依然没有访问文件的许可
Well, we still don't have permission to access files.

520
00:22:13,267 --> 00:22:15,367
要想找到失踪的武器
In order to find missing chemical weapons,

521
00:22:15,436 --> 00:22:17,081
我们得黑进五角大楼
